# Prisma + PostgreSQL

Follow the skill: `.agents/skills/prisma-postgres`

## Schema Conventions

- Use `@map("snake_case")` for column names, PascalCase for model names
- Add `@@map("table_name")` for table names
- Use `@default(uuid())` for IDs
- Add `createdAt`/`updatedAt` with `@default(now())` and `@updatedAt`
- Define `@@index` for foreign keys and frequently filtered columns
- Set `onDelete: Cascade` or `SetNull` explicitly on relations

## Query Conventions

- Use the singleton pattern from `src/config/prisma.ts` — never instantiate `new PrismaClient()` elsewhere
- Use `select` or `include` to limit fields — never fetch everything
- Use `findUniqueOrThrow` / `findFirstOrThrow` when absence is an error
- Use interactive `$transaction` for multi-step writes with business logic
- Handle `PrismaClientKnownRequestError` by code: `P2002` = unique constraint, `P2025` = not found

## Workflow

- Run `npx prisma generate` after every schema change
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name <description>` for migrations
- Use `npx prisma migrate deploy` in CI/production
